The paper proposes a method for estimating local function complexity using a mixture of experts consisting of multinomial kernel logistic regression and Gaussian process regression models. This method is applicable to regression problems and can be used for model interpretation and active learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
